<title>ITALY: Milan AEM power utility prepares for privatisation.</title>
<headline>Milan AEM power utility prepares for privatisation.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Milan gas and electricity utility AEM on Tuesday formally becomes a joint stock company, or SpA, ahead of its privatisation and bourse listing due later this year.</p>
<p>The utility, Azienda Energetica Municipale, has been valued at 1.9 trillion lire, a company source said.</p>
<p>An advisor for the future share placing is expected to be named soon. The city aims to float some 49 percent of the company.</p>
<p>AEM made a net profit of 70.1 billion lire in 1995 on a turnover of 1.02 trillion lire.</p>
<p>Genoa's water and gas utility AMGA made its debut on the Milan bourse this week, the first Italian municipal utility to be floated.</p>
